    U

    union(UnionFindNode<D>, UnionFindNode<D>) - Method in class datastructure.unionfind.QuickFind
    Performs the union of two sets represented by two nodes (if the nodes are not representatives, or they are identical nothing is done); Cost: O(n) where n is the number of nodes in the data structure.
    union(UnionFindNode<D>, UnionFindNode<D>) - Method in class datastructure.unionfind.QuickFindSize
    Performs the union of two sets represented by two nodes by using the heuristic on the size: it checks what is the shortest list to concatenate and updates the pointers to the root only for its elements (if the nodes are not representatives, or they are identical nothing is done); Amortized Cost: O(log n) where n is the number of nodes in the data structure Worst-case: Θ(n) Best-case: O(1)
    union(UnionFindNode<D>, UnionFindNode<D>) - Method in class datastructure.unionfind.QuickUnion
    Performs the union of two sets represented by two nodes, by pointing the parent pointer of the second representative to the first representative (if the nodes are not representatives, or they are identical nothing is done); Cost: O(1)
    union(UnionFindNode<D>, UnionFindNode<D>) - Method in class datastructure.unionfind.QuickUnionRank
    Performs the union of two sets represented by two nodes by using the heuristic on the rank: it checks the ranks of the representatives and avoids to increase the rank of the new set if possible (if the nodes are not representatives, or they are identical nothing is done); Cost: O(1)
    union(UnionFindNode<D>, UnionFindNode<D>) - Method in interface datastructure.unionfind.UnionFind
    Performs the union of two sets represented by two nodes.
